The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Paralympics tragedy

Athens: The Athens Paralympics cancelled celebrations during the closing ceremony after seven schoolchildren travelling to watch the event died in a bus crash on Monday. 

The school bus collided with a truck. Thirty people were injured, 26 of them pupils in their mid-teens, police said. 

?The Paralympics Organising Committee announces the cancellation of celebrations at the closing ceremony (on Tuesday) ... due to the tragic accident,? a statement said. 

